@bizarro12345  So, it’s not mandatory to rename obs64.exe to something else, like ShellHost.exe, right? Also, I’ve already modified the details of obs64.exe so that it appears to be a Microsoft application.

I’ve already tried remote access, but the connection keeps dropping. When I open the link on my PC, the stream works fine, but when I open it from another device, like my phone, the connection gets interrupted. I figured out this happens because of the internet connection, since it’s sending around 12–20 Mbps. Is there a way to compress the streaming video, like OBS does?

Also, I noticed a bug: even though the “copy video URL,” “room ID,” and “chat room” buttons show that the content has been copied, when I try to paste, nothing is actually there (no link, etc.).
